The paper deals with the problem of dynamic spectrum access in cognitive radio systems, which involves signal processing, networking, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. The paper also involves networking aspects, such as channel selection and interference management, which are covered in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of learning algorithms suggests the involvement of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the cooperative aspect of the cognitive users suggests the involvement of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
